People talk about how smartphones are antithetical to literature and art, but the Shazam music app could make part of the plot of a favorite romantic detective mystery. Someone very briefly meets a woman and falls in love with her, she plays him an unusual song on her phone.

He loses her and doesn't even learn her name, the song remains stuck in his mind. Years later he hears it randomly at a bar and Shazams it, it's very niche, he somehow manages to use that information to find who she is and seeks her. What follows: wild danger, adventure, romance.
